1
00:00:08,583 --> 00:00:11,083
[STORE OWNER] Go ahead and
make yourselves comfortable.

2
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:17,000
[YONA] And so began the longest
and darkest night of our lives.

3
00:00:17,083 --> 00:00:18,666
[BOTH yelp]

4
00:00:18,750 --> 00:00:21,625
[YONA] One day remained
before our true battle.

5
00:00:27,125 --> 00:00:29,250
[YONA]
What's going on?

6
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:34,000
Are we being taken to
the ship? I'm so scared.

7
00:00:35,958 --> 00:00:38,458
And what's the situation
with the latest stock?

8
00:00:38,541 --> 00:00:40,000
[OFFICER A]
All accounted for, Sir.

9
00:00:40,083 --> 00:00:42,583
I was told that two very
attractive units showed up

10
00:00:42,666 --> 00:00:44,541
at the shop late this afternoon.

11
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:46,750
Apparently one of them
has bright red hair,

12
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:48,500
which could fetch a high price.

13
00:00:48,583 --> 00:00:50,416
Oh?

14
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:53,208
Good, I can't wait to
see just how much.

15
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,250
[YONA, YUN gasp]

16
00:02:31,375 --> 00:02:33,375
[YONA]
There are so many of them.

17
00:02:33,458 --> 00:02:35,458
How can these men
get away with this?

18
00:02:35,541 --> 00:02:36,791
Get your asses in there now!

19
00:02:36,875 --> 00:02:38,416
[YUN, YONA yelp]

20
00:02:41,416 --> 00:02:43,166
[YONA yelps]

21
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:47,208
Hey, what happened?

22
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:48,875
It looks like you sprained it.

23
00:02:48,958 --> 00:02:51,791
You're gonna have to be extra
careful not to make it worse.

24
00:02:51,875 --> 00:02:53,416
[YONA]
What horrible luck.

25
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:56,541
I can't let it get in the
way of saving these women.

26
00:02:56,625 --> 00:02:59,166
I'll just have to push
through the pain.

27
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,000
[YONA]
It's him... Yang Keum-ji.

28
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:14,250
They weren't lying. This looks
like the best batch yet.

29
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:17,125
My pockets will be lined
with the Kai Empire's money.

30
00:03:17,208 --> 00:03:19,750
[GIRL A] Lord Keum-ji, will we
be taken to our jobs soon?

31
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:21,250
My family is starving.

32
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:23,333
I want to get to work
so that I can help them.

33
00:03:23,416 --> 00:03:25,041
Oh, you'll be working all right.

34
00:03:25,125 --> 00:03:28,458
You'll have more jobs than
you could possibly handle.

35
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:30,000
[gasps]

36
00:03:30,083 --> 00:03:32,083
[KEUM-JI] So, you're the
rare little redhead, then.

37
00:03:32,166 --> 00:03:34,333
You're gonna fetch
me a hefty price...

38
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:36,958
...if I don't decide
to keep you for myself.

39
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:39,666
It'd be kinda sad to let
such a pretty face get away.

40
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:40,958
[YUN]
Yona!

41
00:03:41,041 --> 00:03:43,208
I'd usually pick
money over novelty,

42
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:46,291
but I've only seen a redhead
like you once before in my life.

43
00:03:46,375 --> 00:03:48,708
I could deal with
less gold to have you.

44
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:49,833
[YUN]
Lord Keum-ji!

45
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:50,833
[KEUM-JI]
Huh?

46
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:52,958
Sir, why don't you
take me instead?

47
00:03:53,041 --> 00:03:54,333
You can make your money on her

48
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:56,250
and still keep a
beauty for yourself.

49
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,625
What the heck?

50
00:03:57,708 --> 00:04:00,041
What are these words that're
comin' outta my mouth?

51
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:01,125
Oh yeah?

52
00:04:01,208 --> 00:04:02,666
[YUN]
She's not the one that you want.

53
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,625
I can satisfy you much better.

54
00:04:04,708 --> 00:04:06,500
What's with me?
I don't wanna die!

55
00:04:06,583 --> 00:04:09,333
If he finds out I'm a guy,
he'll rip off what makes me one!

56
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:13,166
[YUN]
But I promised to protect Yona.

57
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:16,166
So let him kill me if he wants.

58
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:19,291
I'd like to let you prove
that to me, sweetheart.

59
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:20,208
However...

60
00:04:20,291 --> 00:04:21,250
[YUN yelps]

61
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:23,750
[coughs]

62
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:26,500
--[GIRLS yelping]
--[YUN groaning]

63
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:27,833
Don't interrupt me again,

64
00:04:27,916 --> 00:04:30,125
or I'll make it so you
never speak another word.

65
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:32,583
Lord Keum-ji, be careful
with the product.

66
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:33,458
[OFFICER A grunts]

67
00:04:33,541 --> 00:04:35,666
--[thud]
--[OFFICER A grunts]

68
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:39,791
When I say don't interrupt
me, that means you, too.

69
00:04:39,875 --> 00:04:42,958
That's right, shut up
and take it. Ha, ha, ha.

70
00:04:43,041 --> 00:04:46,416
As the product, you're to keep
silent and do exactly as I say,

71
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:47,750
is that clear?

72
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:50,500
Take your cues from
little red here, ladies.

73
00:04:53,125 --> 00:04:54,041
[KEUM-JI gasps]

74
00:04:54,125 --> 00:04:55,500
[YONA yelps]

75
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:57,291
[KEUM-JI]
What the--?

76
00:04:57,375 --> 00:05:03,166
Her eyes... Something in
them shook me to the core.

77
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:05,250
I wonder...

78
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:09,250
Redhead, were you born
and raised in Awa's port?

79
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:10,625
[YONA]
Yes, sir.

80
00:05:10,708 --> 00:05:12,375
I've only ever met
one other person

81
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:15,291
with crimson hair like
yours in my lifetime.

82
00:05:15,375 --> 00:05:18,458
She was the young daughter
of the late King Il.

83
00:05:18,541 --> 00:05:19,875
I saw her from afar,

84
00:05:19,958 --> 00:05:23,125
but the sun glinting off
her fiery hair drew my eye.

85
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:26,416
It was the most majestic
thing I'd ever seen.

86
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:28,375
Her name was Yona.

87
00:05:28,458 --> 00:05:31,541
If I remember correctly,
she'd be about your age.

88
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:34,000
Surely this can't
be a coincidence.

89
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,666
Are you Princess Yona?

90
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:37,416
[YUN]
He's found us out.

91
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,250
[YONA]
I'm no princess.

92
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:44,000
My father is a poor
merchant in Awa.

93
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:48,875
I came to the store looking for
extra work to support my family.

94
00:05:48,958 --> 00:05:50,666
I've never heard of this
red-haired princess

95
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:51,958
you speak of.

96
00:05:52,041 --> 00:05:54,125
But, since you think
I look like her,

97
00:05:54,208 --> 00:05:57,666
I could impersonate her and go
by Princess Yona if you'd like.

98
00:05:57,750 --> 00:06:00,708
I wish nothing more than
to bring you joy, my Lord.

99
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:08,208
[KEUM-JI]
Hm.

100
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:10,375
Don't you know a joke
when you hear one?

101
00:06:10,458 --> 00:06:12,458
I was obviously
making fun of you.

102
00:06:12,541 --> 00:06:14,291
How could you think
you're like a princess,

103
00:06:14,375 --> 00:06:16,083
groveling in the dirt?

104
00:06:16,166 --> 00:06:18,791
You're clearly a peasant
with no dignity.

105
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:21,500
Pigs have more
self-respect than that.

106
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,333
Now, pick yourself up.

107
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:24,500
[KEUM-JI]
What nonsense.

108
00:06:24,583 --> 00:06:26,208
I don't know what
I was thinking.

109
00:06:26,291 --> 00:06:27,791
It's only a coincidence.

110
00:06:27,875 --> 00:06:31,166
Besides, I heard the princess
died when she fled the castle.

111
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:34,083
No girl who lived her whole life
under the protection of the king

112
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:37,708
would ever have the power
to shake me, even for a moment.

113
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:41,166
But this girl has the eyes
of a caged, wild animal.

114
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:42,416
[chuckles]

115
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:45,458
[OFFICER A groaning]

116
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:46,750
[GIRLS sighing]

117
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:48,875
[YONA]
Yun, are you hurt?

118
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:52,541
Ugh.

119
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,791
What kinda man would ever
hit a delicate flower like me?

120
00:06:54,875 --> 00:06:56,291
I know.

121
00:06:56,375 --> 00:07:00,083
Your ankle. The swelling's
gotten much worse. Does it hurt?

122
00:07:00,166 --> 00:07:01,833
No, it doesn't.

123
00:07:01,916 --> 00:07:03,791
I forgot about it, actually.

124
00:07:03,875 --> 00:07:06,041
I'm gonna put my
pain to good use.

125
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:08,500
I'll remember it and
bring it right back to 'im.

126
00:07:08,583 --> 00:07:11,208
Keum-ji is gonna
feel the hurt tenfold.

127
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:13,708
[GIRL B] I don't understand
what he meant earlier.

128
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:17,166
A "hefty price"?
Are we going to be sold?

129
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:20,541
Help me! Get me out
of here right now!

130
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:22,791
Please come and open the door!

131
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:24,208
I'm begging you!
I don't wanna...

132
00:07:24,291 --> 00:07:26,291
[GIRL]
It's no use.

133
00:07:26,375 --> 00:07:27,541
No one's gonna save you,

134
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:30,250
no matter how much you
scream and cry for help.

135
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:34,250
I've been here for two weeks,
trapped like an animal.

136
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:36,541
To Keum-ji, we're nothing
more than livestock.

137
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:39,291
We'll be sold to whoever's
the highest bidder.

138
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:43,750
It's no surprise. Awa has
always been a corrupt cesspool.

139
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:50,875
[YONA] And you're content
to accept that, are you?

140
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:51,875
Accept what?

141
00:07:51,958 --> 00:07:53,500
[YONA]
The corruption.

142
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:57,583
You could do something.
Save Awa from men like him.

143
00:07:57,666 --> 00:07:59,166
Restore the power to the people

144
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:02,083
and end the reign of terror that
has plagued you for so long.

145
00:08:02,166 --> 00:08:03,916
[GIRLS gasping]

146
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:07,875
[GIRL] Ha. There's no way you
are from anywhere around Awa.

147
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:09,666
Because if you
had grown up here,

148
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:12,416
you'd know how ridiculous
you sound saying that.

149
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:15,166
Try to fight. You won't
make it out alive.

150
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:18,625
You may be right about
me being a foreigner,

151
00:08:18,708 --> 00:08:20,291
but I care about this town.

152
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:24,333
People I love are fighting for
it now, and we're gonna win.

153
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:25,833
[GIRLS gasping]

154
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:28,458
Except we're trapped in a
cellar, facing certain death.

155
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:30,791
Yeah, we're definitely on
the winning side of this fight.

156
00:08:30,875 --> 00:08:33,708
Why do you always have
to be so sarcastic?

157
00:08:33,791 --> 00:08:35,583
So you really think
there's hope?

158
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:38,083
Someone might actually
be able to save us?

159
00:08:38,166 --> 00:08:40,416
That's the dumbest
thing you've said yet.

160
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:43,291
You might think
it's stupid, but still.

161
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:45,208
If there's any chance
we can be saved,

162
00:08:45,291 --> 00:08:46,791
they'll do it.

163
00:08:46,875 --> 00:08:50,583
You just have to trust me, and
put your life in their hands.

164
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:56,333
If you wanna make it
out alive, have faith.

165
00:08:56,416 --> 00:08:57,375
[YUN]
Hm.

166
00:08:58,458 --> 00:09:01,625
If we just keep
fighting, we'll survive.

167
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:03,291
[gasps]

168
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:05,583
[GIRLS gasping]

169
00:09:05,666 --> 00:09:07,750
[YONA]
I know I have limitations.

170
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:10,041
At heart, I'm
just a regular girl.

171
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:14,416
I can't change that, but I can
control how I affect others.

172
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:16,166
I'm willing to lay down my life

173
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,666
if it'll make the
world a better place.

174
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:21,291
Please, you have to
help me fight for you.

175
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:24,958
Together, we can end
this reign of terror.

176
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:48,625
[JEAHA]
Hak.

177
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:50,833
Why don't you go
and lie down, huh?

178
00:09:50,916 --> 00:09:52,333
You've been scanning
the harbor since she left--

179
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:54,916
This is what resting
looks like for me.

180
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,625
Besides, just look
at White Snake.

181
00:09:56,708 --> 00:09:58,333
You should be worried
about that mess.

182
00:09:58,416 --> 00:09:59,625
[JEAHA]
Huh?

183
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:01,041
--Hey, buddy, lemme take you
--I swear to you!

184
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:02,708
--to your bunk, okay?
--If he so much as touches her.

185
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:03,833
[JEAHA]
The heck's that about?

186
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:05,916
He dozes off for a few minutes.

187
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,375
Then all of a sudden,
he'll jump up

188
00:10:07,458 --> 00:10:08,916
and pick a fight with the air.

189
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,458
Sheesh, that's rough.

190
00:10:10,541 --> 00:10:13,958
He needs to develop some coping
strategies. He looks awful.

191
00:10:14,041 --> 00:10:15,291
You're tired, too.

192
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:17,541
You need sleep. A lot.

193
00:10:17,625 --> 00:10:20,541
Uh! Why'd you have to go and
whisper creepily in my ear?

194
00:10:20,625 --> 00:10:22,000
Watch it, weirdo!

195
00:10:22,083 --> 00:10:24,916
But it's the truth.
You look tired.

196
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,708
What do you mean?
I look great. At least,

197
00:10:27,791 --> 00:10:30,000
that's what all the ladies
were telling me last night.

198
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:32,333
As I remember, we
passed out pretty early.

199
00:10:32,416 --> 00:10:34,958
I musta worn 'em
out as usual. Eh?

200
00:10:35,041 --> 00:10:36,458
[JEAHA yelling]

201
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:38,125
--[HAK] Show us your face.
--[GIJA] Stop hiding from us!

202
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:39,916
[HAK]
Lemme look at your eyes!

203
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,833
[JEAHA moans]

204
00:10:44,916 --> 00:10:46,458
You've defiled me.

205
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:49,208
I'm just an object for you
to use and I think I like it.

206
00:10:49,291 --> 00:10:50,375
Clothes on.

207
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:52,541
You're tired, too!
You don't have to lie!

208
00:10:52,625 --> 00:10:54,041
If you'd stayed up late
with those ladies,

209
00:10:54,125 --> 00:10:55,333
you'd feel the same way.

210
00:10:55,416 --> 00:10:56,875
[SINHA]
I saw you.

211
00:10:56,958 --> 00:10:59,750
You were in the crow's nest
all night, staring at the water.

212
00:10:59,833 --> 00:11:01,666
So, you're stalking me now?

213
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,041
I gotta say.

214
00:11:03,125 --> 00:11:05,000
I'm incredibly flattered, Sinha.

215
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:07,083
Look, we all know that
you're worried about Yona,

216
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:08,375
just like the rest of us.

217
00:11:08,458 --> 00:11:09,833
Yeah, of course I am!

218
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:12,583
We sent the poor kid right
into the belly of the beast.

219
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:16,250
Waiting is torture. I'm dying
to know whether she's okay.

220
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:18,083
That's what I wanna hear.

221
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:20,875
If you care about her
even half as much as I do,

222
00:11:20,958 --> 00:11:22,250
you're okay by me.

223
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:26,208
You can stand by my side
in battle any day, brother.

224
00:11:26,291 --> 00:11:28,333
Whatever you say.

225
00:11:28,416 --> 00:11:31,041
In any case, what about the
other kid we sent with her?

226
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:33,833
Yun, right? I'm not so
sure he can handle it.

227
00:11:33,916 --> 00:11:35,541
He seems kinda fragile.

228
00:11:35,625 --> 00:11:38,041
You sure we can trust
him to keep Yona safe?

229
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:39,750
'Cause I have my doubts.

230
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:41,625
Don't underestimate Yun.

231
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:42,958
Yeah.

232
00:11:43,041 --> 00:11:45,833
He isn't just some ordinary
kid. No, not at all.

233
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:49,458
He's proven himself. I'd trust
him with my life no problem.

234
00:11:49,541 --> 00:11:50,500
[SINHA]
Mm.

235
00:11:56,125 --> 00:11:57,375
[GI-GANG chuckles]

236
00:11:57,458 --> 00:11:58,708
[window howling]

237
00:11:58,791 --> 00:12:00,041
[GI-GANG]
Hm?

238
00:12:00,125 --> 00:12:01,333
Sinha!

239
00:12:05,208 --> 00:12:06,833
[SINHA]
I can see Keum-ji's ships.

240
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:09,000
They're headed this way.

241
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:11,541
All right, rascals.
Weapons ready.

242
00:12:14,791 --> 00:12:16,333
This is it.

243
00:12:16,416 --> 00:12:19,458
Tonight we fight what will be
our most important battle ever.

244
00:12:23,166 --> 00:12:24,750
We all know what's at stake.

245
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:27,125
Let's bring back
Yang Keum-Ji's head!

246
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:30,083
[PIRATES]
Yeah!

247
00:12:35,125 --> 00:12:36,083
Ao.

248
00:12:45,250 --> 00:12:46,916
[knocking]

249
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,333
Hey! Keep it down in there!

250
00:12:49,416 --> 00:12:50,500
Huh?

251
00:12:52,541 --> 00:12:55,083
So, which one of you is
makin' all the noise? Uh!

252
00:12:57,833 --> 00:12:59,375
[LOOKOUT]
You're gonna pay for that.

253
00:12:59,458 --> 00:13:01,875
How the hell did you
get outta the ropes?

254
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,375
Whaddaya think you're
gonna do with that--?

255
00:13:04,458 --> 00:13:05,500
This!

256
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:10,375
[GIRL A]
Did you kill him?

257
00:13:10,458 --> 00:13:12,458
[YUN]
No, it's only a sedative,

258
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:15,750
but he'll be out a while.
For twelve hours at least.

259
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,708
We still need to
act quickly, though.

260
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:22,375
I can't believe it. You're
actually planning to escape?

261
00:13:27,875 --> 00:13:30,500
What is it? Why are
you trembling?

262
00:13:30,583 --> 00:13:33,583
Your ankle. It looks
pretty awful.

263
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:36,750
Are you sure you're gonna be
able to go through with this?

264
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:41,250
If you get caught, you might
get every one of us killed.

265
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:45,666
Don't worry. We have an
entire army behind us.

266
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:47,375
Seriously?

267
00:13:47,458 --> 00:13:50,666
Maybe not an army exactly,
but a ship full of allies.

268
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,416
We need to send
them our location.

269
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:55,583
But how? We sailed out
to sea a while ago.

270
00:13:55,666 --> 00:13:57,500
We're in the middle
of the ocean now.

271
00:13:57,583 --> 00:14:00,291
How do you expect them
to find us out here?

272
00:14:00,375 --> 00:14:03,083
We're going out on the
deck to send up a flare.

273
00:14:03,166 --> 00:14:04,583
[GIRL]
What?

274
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:06,041
It's a small firework,

275
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:08,583
but our friends can
see it from miles away.

276
00:14:08,666 --> 00:14:12,083
I've a feeling they're
not too far from here.

277
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:15,625
Have hope. I promise
we'll save you.

278
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:18,208
Let's go.

279
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:19,708
'Kay.

280
00:14:19,791 --> 00:14:21,250
[groaning]

281
00:14:30,875 --> 00:14:34,208
And you're content to
accept that, are you?

282
00:14:37,166 --> 00:14:39,000
Hold on!

283
00:14:39,083 --> 00:14:42,250
The deck is crawling
with Keum-ji's men.

284
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,250
Let me go with
you, I can help.

285
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:45,583
[BOTH gasp]

286
00:14:45,666 --> 00:14:47,291
[GIRL]
Please, hear me out.

287
00:14:47,375 --> 00:14:48,750
My father's
a shipyard carpenter,

288
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:50,916
so I grew up around
boats like this one.

289
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,541
I can help you stay hidden.

290
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:53,750
Thank you so much.

291
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:55,916
You wanna help? But why?

292
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,500
[GIRL] Because what your friend
said earlier really hit home.

293
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:00,166
All these years we've
watched our people

294
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:04,791
be terrorized by Yang Keum-ji.
It's time for us to fight back.

295
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:08,500
[GIRL]
Are you with me?

296
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:15,166
My name is Yuri, what's yours?

297
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:18,583
Oh, my name is... uh... Lina.

298
00:15:18,666 --> 00:15:20,375
And I-- Uh.

299
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:23,958
My name is Yun. I'm the brains
behind this operation.

300
00:15:24,041 --> 00:15:25,833
I find that hard to believe.

301
00:15:25,916 --> 00:15:28,958
[MERCENARIES yelling]

302
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:30,416
Sounds like they're here.

303
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:31,625
Yeah, sure does.

304
00:15:31,708 --> 00:15:34,166
[yelling]

305
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:39,208
[MERCENARIES grunting]

306
00:15:39,291 --> 00:15:42,583
[MERCENARY F yelling]

307
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:44,208
[GIJA]
Bring me to Keum-ji!

308
00:15:44,291 --> 00:15:47,125
I'll take his head,
and send the rest to hell!

309
00:15:47,208 --> 00:15:48,375
[HAK]
Hate to break it to you,

310
00:15:48,458 --> 00:15:49,916
but sometimes it's hard
to take you seriously,

311
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,875
--[HAK] White Snake.
--Don't call me White Snake!

312
00:15:51,958 --> 00:15:53,750
Sinha, where's the princess?

313
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:55,625
I dunno. I can't see her.

314
00:15:55,708 --> 00:15:57,833
[MERCENARY H yelling]

315
00:15:57,916 --> 00:15:59,458
You better go easy on 'em.

316
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:01,208
You don't want the
old lady throwin' a fit.

317
00:16:01,291 --> 00:16:03,166
I'd watch my tongue
if I were you.

318
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:05,541
Call the captain old and
she's liable to kill you.

319
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:06,416
[MERCENARIES yelling]

320
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:07,958
How'd Keum-ji find so many men?

321
00:16:08,041 --> 00:16:09,958
I'm willing to bet that
he hired mercenaries

322
00:16:10,041 --> 00:16:11,791
from all over the kingdom.

323
00:16:11,875 --> 00:16:12,833
[gasps]

324
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,625
[MERCENARY K groans]

325
00:16:16,708 --> 00:16:20,500
Where are you? We're ready.
Send up the signal.

326
00:16:20,583 --> 00:16:22,875
Crap. We're totally outnumbered!

327
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:24,583
They're not showin'
signs of letting up.

328
00:16:24,666 --> 00:16:27,250
He never had this
many men in the past.

329
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,000
[MAYA]
Jeaha!

330
00:16:29,083 --> 00:16:31,250
You ladies decide
to take a time out?

331
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:33,791
We were just...
doin' a quick recon!

332
00:16:36,458 --> 00:16:38,000
You ever notice
how he flies away

333
00:16:38,083 --> 00:16:40,166
any time he doesn't
have a good come-back?

334
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:43,333
I'm pretty sure flying
away is his come-back.

335
00:16:43,416 --> 00:16:45,916
Funny. I'm not even mad.

336
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:50,083
[BOTH yelling]

337
00:16:50,166 --> 00:16:52,583
[OFFICER D] Guess the pirates
finally decided to attack.

338
00:16:52,666 --> 00:16:54,833
It should be over
pretty quickly, though,

339
00:16:54,916 --> 00:16:57,041
since we've got all
of those mercenaries.

340
00:16:57,125 --> 00:16:59,833
Those idiots don't
stand a chance. Huh?

341
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:02,000
How did you get out?

342
00:17:02,083 --> 00:17:03,666
You'd better get back
down below or else!

343
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:04,708
[OFFICER D]
Hold it!

344
00:17:05,791 --> 00:17:08,291
What an idiot.
That's a dead end.

345
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:10,416
Give up now!

346
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,666
[BOTH yelp, grunt]

347
00:17:14,125 --> 00:17:15,708
[YUN]
Aw, that looks painful.

348
00:17:15,791 --> 00:17:17,250
Let me help. You'll feel better.

349
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:17,916
[ship creaks]

350
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:18,708
[yelps]

351
00:17:18,791 --> 00:17:20,791
[BOTH gasp]

352
00:17:20,875 --> 00:17:22,291
[OFFICER C grunts]

353
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:24,208
Oh, no!

354
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:25,125
Stay back!

355
00:17:25,208 --> 00:17:27,166
Yuri!

356
00:17:27,250 --> 00:17:30,000
Keum-ji wouldn't like it if
you damaged his merchandise.

357
00:17:30,083 --> 00:17:32,416
So, why don't you let her go
and we can have a chat.

358
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:33,750
We could help each other.

359
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:36,291
I refuse to negotiate
with damaged cargo.

360
00:17:36,375 --> 00:17:39,166
I'm gonna kill you to teach
the people of Awa a lesson.

361
00:17:39,250 --> 00:17:41,083
No one disobeys Keum-ji.

362
00:17:41,166 --> 00:17:42,166
[YONA]
Let her go!

363
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:44,083
She had nothing to do with this!

364
00:17:44,166 --> 00:17:45,583
[YUN] 
We're trapped.

365
00:17:45,666 --> 00:17:47,958
And I've got the signal flare.

366
00:17:48,041 --> 00:17:51,458
I could break free,
rush up on deck, and fire it.

367
00:17:51,541 --> 00:17:53,000
No, that won't work.

368
00:17:53,083 --> 00:17:56,541
I can't leave Yona and Yuri
to the mercy of these monsters.

369
00:17:56,625 --> 00:17:58,708
They'd kill them both for sure.

370
00:17:58,791 --> 00:18:01,125
Think, Yun, think!

371
00:18:01,208 --> 00:18:02,583
I've gotta get these
guys outta the way

372
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:05,166
and get us up onto the deck.

373
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:10,041
Come on. Come on. Come on!

374
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:14,916
[YUN]
There was a time

375
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,250
when I would've just
broke free and run,

376
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:19,375
not caring enough to
save anyone but myself.

377
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:20,916
I could escape right now

378
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:25,125
if I didn't care about Yona,
Yuri, and the others, but I do.

379
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:28,625
[YUN]
Ik-su,

380
00:18:28,708 --> 00:18:31,333
I think you would be proud
of the man I've become.

381
00:18:33,291 --> 00:18:35,083
[YUN] I'm part of
something bigger now.

382
00:18:35,166 --> 00:18:36,291
[ALL gasp]

383
00:18:36,375 --> 00:18:39,083
[YUN] Something much
bigger than just myself.

384
00:18:39,166 --> 00:18:40,750
[YUN]
I'm the one that you want.

385
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,791
As you can see, I'm not
what you thought.

386
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:44,666
I forced these two to help me.

387
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,375
You should just let them go.

388
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:47,458
That's a guy?!

389
00:18:47,541 --> 00:18:49,541
I'm an undercover spy
for the pirates.

390
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:51,000
I was sent to
infiltrate this ship

391
00:18:51,083 --> 00:18:52,916
to give away your
exact location.

392
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,083
The pirates sent you?

393
00:18:54,166 --> 00:18:55,583
[OFFICER D]
You little brat!

394
00:18:55,666 --> 00:18:58,208
You've just made the biggest
mistake of your life!

395
00:18:58,291 --> 00:19:00,375
And I'm gonna make
sure it's your last!

396
00:19:00,458 --> 00:19:02,250
--I'll beat you to death!
--[YONA] Stop it!

397
00:19:04,625 --> 00:19:06,375
[YUN]
Hold on, please.

398
00:19:06,458 --> 00:19:09,041
Listen to me for a second.

399
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:10,541
There's a bomb.

400
00:19:10,625 --> 00:19:13,041
It's hidden on
this ship somewhere.

401
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:15,583
I'm the only one who
knows how to disarm it.

402
00:19:15,666 --> 00:19:17,791
How do I know you're
not messin' with me?

403
00:19:17,875 --> 00:19:19,166
Well, I could be,

404
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:20,958
but are you sure you're
willing to take the chance?

405
00:19:21,041 --> 00:19:22,291
[OFFICER C] 
Don't be stupid.

406
00:19:22,375 --> 00:19:24,208
You really think we'd
fall for that crap?

407
00:19:24,291 --> 00:19:25,625
I've got nothing to lose.

408
00:19:25,708 --> 00:19:28,791
Believe me or don't,
it's your life at stake.

409
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:30,791
[YUN]
I've gotta get out on deck.

410
00:19:30,875 --> 00:19:34,041
If I can send up the signal,
Sinha's bound to see it.

411
00:19:34,125 --> 00:19:36,833
It's our only chance
of being saved.

412
00:19:36,916 --> 00:19:38,666
Whaddaya think?

413
00:19:38,750 --> 00:19:40,083
Dammit!

414
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:42,750
Take the girls back down below
and tie them up tight.

415
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:44,166
I'll take him up on deck.

416
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:45,666
And then we'll find the bomb.

417
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:47,166
[OFFICER D]
But...

418
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:48,833
[OFFICER C] Doesn't matter
whether there's a bomb or not.

419
00:19:48,916 --> 00:19:50,625
I'm gonna cut off this
kid's pretty little head

420
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:53,916
and send it back to
his dirty pirate friends.

421
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:54,750
Get up!

422
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:55,500
[YONA]
Yun!

423
00:19:55,583 --> 00:19:57,958
Hey! Stay back!

424
00:19:58,041 --> 00:20:01,458
[yelping]

425
00:20:01,541 --> 00:20:02,458
[gasps]

426
00:20:02,541 --> 00:20:04,333
[OFFICER C]
All right. Let's go.

427
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,875
Just what in the hell
do you think you're doing?

428
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:11,541
Ah! Dammit!

429
00:20:11,625 --> 00:20:13,416
[YONA yelps, grunts]

430
00:20:20,041 --> 00:20:21,750
Don't you da--

431
00:20:23,958 --> 00:20:26,166
[OFFICER C]
Where's the bomb? Well?

432
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:28,416
I knew it, you were
just bluffing!

433
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:29,583
I told you.

434
00:20:29,666 --> 00:20:31,166
It's somewhere near the bow.

435
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:35,541
At least, that's what they said.
Let me up and I'll show you.

436
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:37,166
[YUN]
If I set off the firework here,

437
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,916
I'm not sure that Sinha
will be able to see it.

438
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,333
I've gotta get out
in the open to light it.

439
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,416
[OFFICER C] I had a feelin'
you were lyin' to us.

440
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:53,125
Guess I'll make an example out
of you after all, pretty boy.

441
00:20:53,208 --> 00:20:54,916
Say your prayers.

442
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,375
[OFFICERS gasping]

443
00:21:03,291 --> 00:21:04,875
Yona.

444
00:21:04,958 --> 00:21:07,291
Step away from him right now.

445
00:21:07,375 --> 00:21:09,875
If you don't do what
I say, you're dead.

446
00:21:09,958 --> 00:21:13,000
Oh look, guys. It's the
feisty little redhead.

447
00:21:13,083 --> 00:21:15,750
You think that bow and arrow
are enough to shake us?

448
00:21:19,625 --> 00:21:21,166
[YUN]
Yona!

449
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:22,708
Come and get the firework!

450
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:25,458
Set it off! Use the lantern!

451
00:21:25,541 --> 00:21:26,500
[OFFICERS]
Huh?

452
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:29,208
Ah?!

453
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:33,083
[YONA]
Hey, Yun. You have it?

454
00:21:33,166 --> 00:21:35,250
I've got it hidden
inside of my dress.

455
00:21:38,791 --> 00:21:40,375
[OFFICER C]
Hey! Stop her!

456
00:21:44,291 --> 00:21:45,541
[YONA]
I hope this works!

457
00:21:45,625 --> 00:21:47,208
[YUN]
I hope he sees it!

458
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:53,791
I did it!

459
00:23:33,875 --> 00:23:34,791
[YONA]
Father,

460
00:23:34,875 --> 00:23:36,833
I've become much stronger.

461
00:23:36,916 --> 00:23:39,583
Am I making you proud,
wherever you are?

462
00:23:39,666 --> 00:23:42,041
Next time on Yona of the Dawn,

463
00:23:42,125 --> 00:23:46,041
Episode 22:
"History is Made at Night."

